1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,080
Hello everyone and welcome to EnglishPod.
大家好，欢迎收听EnglishPod。

2
00:00:03,080 --> 00:00:04,080
My name is Marco.
我是Marco。

3
00:00:04,080 --> 00:00:07,720
My name is Catherine and you've probably heard us talking a little bit about small talk the
我是Catherine，你可能已经听到我们过去几周聊了一些关于闲聊的话题。

4
00:00:07,720 --> 00:00:08,720
past few weeks.
过去几周。

5
00:00:08,720 --> 00:00:12,160
We have another episode about small talk and we're going to teach you some things that
我们还有一集关于闲聊的内容，会教你在遇到很久没见或甚至初次见面的人时可以说些什么。

6
00:00:12,160 --> 00:00:16,640
you can say to people when you haven't seen them or maybe even met them before.
你可以在遇到很久没见或甚至初次见面的人时使用。

7
00:00:16,640 --> 00:00:17,640
That's right.
没错。

8
00:00:17,640 --> 00:00:18,920
Today we're going to talk to a stranger.
今天我们要和一个陌生人聊天。

9
00:00:18,920 --> 00:00:23,800
So we're going to talk very briefly about some casual topic.
所以我们会简短地聊一些随意的话题。

10
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:28,000
And so let's jump into the dialogue and see what happens.
那我们就直接进入对话，看看会发生什么。

11
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:36,280
Excuse me, is this seat taken?
打扰一下，这个座位有人吗？

12
00:00:36,280 --> 00:00:37,840
No, please feel free.
没有，请随意。

13
00:00:37,840 --> 00:00:38,840
Thanks a lot.
非常感谢。

14
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,400
Do you work in Shanghai?
你在上海工作吗？

15
00:00:40,400 --> 00:00:41,400
Yes, I do.
是的，我在上海工作。

16
00:00:41,400 --> 00:00:42,400
How about you?
你呢？

17
00:00:42,400 --> 00:00:44,400
No, I'm a tourist.
不，我是游客。

18
00:00:44,400 --> 00:00:45,760
This place is amazing.
这个地方太棒了。

19
00:00:45,760 --> 00:00:48,600
It's much bigger than I imagined and much more exciting.
它比我想象的大得多，也精彩得多。

20
00:00:48,600 --> 00:00:50,160
There's so much to see here.
这里有很多值得看的东西。

21
00:00:50,160 --> 00:00:52,000
You can say that again.
你说得没错。

22
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:54,920
It's much more modern than people imagine.
它比人们想象的现代化得多。

23
00:00:54,920 --> 00:00:55,920
Where are you from?
你从哪里来？

24
00:00:55,920 --> 00:00:57,320
Well, let's see.
嗯，让我想想。

25
00:00:57,320 --> 00:01:01,480
I'm from Kansas originally, a much quieter and more peaceful place than here.
我原本来自堪萨斯，一个比这里安静和平得多的地方。

26
00:01:01,480 --> 00:01:03,200
That's for sure.
确实如此。

27
00:01:03,200 --> 00:01:04,840
But I'm living in Paris right now.
但我现在住在巴黎。

28
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:05,840
Oh, Paris.
哦，巴黎。

29
00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:06,840
Wonderful.
太棒了。

30
00:01:06,840 --> 00:01:09,160
I'd love to visit sometime.
我以后很想去看看。

31
00:01:09,160 --> 00:01:12,300
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

32
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:15,720
So now we're going to take a look at a lot of phrases on this occasion.
现在我们要看看这次对话中的很多短语。

33
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:21,080
So let's go for fluency builder part one.
那我们进入流利度构建第一部分。

34
00:01:21,080 --> 00:01:22,080
Fluency builder.
流利度构建。

35
00:01:22,080 --> 00:01:23,080
All right.
好的。

36
00:01:23,080 --> 00:01:29,440
So the first phrase we have is a very common phrase if you're in a train or on a bus.
第一个短语非常常见，如果你在火车或公交车上。

37
00:01:29,440 --> 00:01:31,720
You hear the phrase, is this seat taken?
你会听到这个短语：这个座位有人吗？

38
00:01:31,720 --> 00:01:32,720
Right.
对。

39
00:01:32,720 --> 00:01:37,640
So Michelle came up to the stranger and said, excuse me, is this seat taken?
所以Michelle走向陌生人说：打扰一下，这个座位有人吗？

40
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,800
That means, is anybody sitting here?
意思是：这里有人坐吗？

41
00:01:39,800 --> 00:01:41,480
It basically means, can I sit here?
基本上就是问：我能坐这儿吗？

42
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:42,480
Right.
对。

43
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:45,280
This is a very polite way of asking if you can sit down in the seat.
这是一种非常礼貌的问法，询问是否可以坐下。

44
00:01:45,280 --> 00:01:49,320
You can also say it in a restaurant, at a movie theater, in a classroom.
你可以在餐厅、电影院、教室里这么说。

45
00:01:49,320 --> 00:01:50,480
So remember this one.
所以记住这个。

46
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:52,520
This was a really, really common phrase.
这是一个非常非常常见的短语。

47
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:55,240
So it's a very polite way of saying, can I sit down?
所以这是一种非常礼貌的说法，意思是：我能坐下吗？

48
00:01:55,240 --> 00:01:56,240
That's right.
没错。

49
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:57,240
You're asking for permission basically.
你基本上是在请求许可。

50
00:01:57,240 --> 00:01:58,320
Is the seat taken?
这个座位有人吗？

51
00:01:58,320 --> 00:02:01,040
Because what if a person says, well, no, it's not.
因为如果对方说：嗯，没有。

52
00:02:01,040 --> 00:02:02,960
Do you have to say, may I sit down?
你是不是要说：我可以坐下吗？

53
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:03,960
May I take a seat?
我可以坐吗？

54
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:06,600
Well, if they say, I'm sorry, someone is sitting here.
嗯，如果他们说：抱歉，有人坐这儿。

55
00:02:06,600 --> 00:02:09,840
That means that maybe they're waiting for a friend and then no, you can't sit there.
那意味着他们可能在等朋友，所以你不能坐那儿。

56
00:02:09,840 --> 00:02:15,560
But if they say, sure, like in the dialogue, feel free, then you're really basically able
但如果他们说：当然，就像对话里的“请随意”，那你基本上就可以坐下了。

57
00:02:15,560 --> 00:02:16,560
to sit down.
坐下。

58
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,560
No problem.
没问题。

59
00:02:17,560 --> 00:02:18,560
Right.
对。

60
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,560
So the stranger answers by saying, no, please feel free.
所以陌生人回答说：没有，请随意。

61
00:02:20,560 --> 00:02:23,200
So he says, no, the seat is not taken.
所以他说：没有，座位没人。

62
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,200
Please feel free.
请随意。

63
00:02:24,200 --> 00:02:25,800
What does he mean by this?
他这是什么意思？

64
00:02:25,800 --> 00:02:26,800
Okay.
好的。

65
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:30,440
Feel free is a very unusual phrase in English, but one that you're going to hear a lot.
“Feel free”在英语中是一个不寻常的短语，但你会经常听到。

66
00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:33,160
It basically means do what you want to do.
它基本上意思是：做你想做的事。

67
00:02:33,160 --> 00:02:34,160
Okay.
好的。

68
00:02:34,160 --> 00:02:35,160
Okay.
好的。

69
00:02:35,160 --> 00:02:37,080
So if I want to sit down, I say, is this seat taken?
所以如果我想坐下，我会说：这个座位有人吗？

70
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:40,240
If you say, feel free, Marco, that means feel free to sit down.
如果你说：随意，Marco，那就意味着随意坐下。

71
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,240
Okay.
好的。

72
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:46,600
So we can complete the sentence by saying, no, please feel free to sit down.
所以我们可以把句子补充完整：没有，请随意坐下。

73
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:49,120
But it's kind of stating the obvious.
但这有点显而易见。

74
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:51,560
You're saying basically feel free to do what you want.
你基本上是在说：随意做你想做的事。

75
00:02:51,560 --> 00:02:52,560
That's right.
没错。

76
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,560
But you could use it in other ways.
但你也可以在其他场合使用它。

77
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:56,760
For example, Hey Marco, are you using this pen right here?
比如：嘿，Marco，你正在用这支笔吗？

78
00:02:56,760 --> 00:02:58,120
No, no, feel free.
没有，没有，随意用。

79
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,520
That means feel free to use my pen.
意思是随意用我的笔。

80
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,520
Okay.
好的。

81
00:03:01,520 --> 00:03:02,520
Very good.
非常好。

82
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:06,920
And so then they started talking about what they do, where they work.
然后他们开始聊各自做什么工作、在哪里工作。

83
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:09,560
And Michelle said, yes, I work in Shanghai.
米歇尔说，是的，我在上海工作。

84
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,880
How about you?
你呢？

85
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:12,160
Oh, how about you?
哦，你呢？

86
00:03:12,160 --> 00:03:15,000
Now this is a really important construction.
这是一个非常重要的结构。

87
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:16,680
This is a really important phrase in English.
这是英语中一个非常重要的短语。

88
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:19,320
And I think a lot of people make mistakes with this.
我觉得很多人会在这里犯错。

89
00:03:19,320 --> 00:03:23,880
So how about you means, do you work in Shanghai?
所以“how about you”的意思是，你在上海工作吗？

90
00:03:23,880 --> 00:03:25,960
I just said I work in Shanghai, but how about you?
我刚说了我在上海工作，但你呢？

91
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:26,960
Do you?
你呢？

92
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:27,960
Right.
对。

93
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:28,960
Exactly.
没错。

94
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,880
So that's saying, and you, do you work here?
所以这相当于说，那你呢，你在这里工作吗？

95
00:03:30,880 --> 00:03:32,800
Or and you, what do you do?
或者，那你呢，你是做什么的？

96
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:33,800
How about you?
你呢？

97
00:03:33,800 --> 00:03:41,400
Now, the common mistake with how about you or using the construction how about is that
关于“how about you”或使用“how about”这个结构，常见的错误是

98
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:46,240
for some reason, some people seem to think that it means how is it?
不知为何，有些人似乎认为它意思是“怎么样？”

99
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:51,360
So for example, if someone says, how about your weekend?
比如，如果有人说“how about your weekend？”

100
00:03:51,360 --> 00:03:52,360
That's wrong.
那是错的。

101
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,360
No, we don't say that.
不，我们不这么说。

102
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,640
How was your weekend?
应该说“how was your weekend？”

103
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:59,440
But in this case, how about you always follows a statement.
但在这种情况下，“how about you”总是跟在陈述句后面。

104
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:00,440
Okay.
好的。

105
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:01,900
So yes, I do live in Shanghai.
所以，是的，我确实住在上海。

106
00:04:01,900 --> 00:04:02,900
How about you?
你呢？

107
00:04:02,900 --> 00:04:04,360
That means, do you live in Shanghai?
这意思是，你住在上海吗？

108
00:04:04,360 --> 00:04:05,360
Right.
对。

109
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:08,460
If I say, I would like to eat a hamburger and French fries.
如果我说，我想吃一个汉堡和薯条。

110
00:04:08,460 --> 00:04:09,460
How about you?
你呢？

111
00:04:09,460 --> 00:04:10,460
How about you?
你呢？

112
00:04:10,460 --> 00:04:11,460
What would you like to eat?
你想吃什么？

113
00:04:11,460 --> 00:04:12,460
Exactly.
没错。

114
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:15,000
So remember, that's the way that you use how about.
所以记住，这就是你使用“how about”的方式。

115
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:20,560
Never say how about your weekend or how about your vacation when you want to ask, how was
永远不要说“how about your weekend”或“how about your vacation”当你想问“怎么样”时，

116
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,560
it?
怎么样？

117
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:22,560
Don't say that.
别那么说。

118
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:27,120
No, basically, this is a way to reply to someone when they're telling you about their experience.
不，基本上，这是一种回应别人的方式，当他们告诉你他们的经历时。

119
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:28,880
You want to talk about yours.
你想谈谈你的经历。

120
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:29,880
That's right.
没错。

121
00:04:29,880 --> 00:04:31,640
Okay, so let's take a break.
好的，那我们休息一下。

122
00:04:31,640 --> 00:04:42,400
Let's review everything and we'll be back with Fluency Builder part two.
我们来回顾一下所有内容，然后回来继续流畅表达第二部分。

123
00:04:42,400 --> 00:04:44,520
Excuse me, is this seat taken?
打扰一下，这个座位有人吗？

124
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:46,080
No, please feel free.
没有，请随意。

125
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:47,200
Thanks a lot.
非常感谢。

126
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:48,720
Do you work in Shanghai?
你在上海工作吗？

127
00:04:48,720 --> 00:04:50,440
Yes, I do.
是的，我在上海工作。

128
00:04:50,440 --> 00:04:51,440
How about you?
你呢？

129
00:04:51,440 --> 00:04:52,720
No, I'm a tourist.
不，我是游客。

130
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,060
This place is amazing.
这个地方太棒了。

131
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:56,880
It's much bigger than I imagined and much more exciting.
它比我想象的大得多，也刺激得多。

132
00:04:56,880 --> 00:04:58,480
There's so much to see here.
这里有很多可看的东西。

133
00:04:58,480 --> 00:05:00,280
You can say that again.
你说得太对了。

134
00:05:00,280 --> 00:05:03,240
It's much more modern than people imagine.
它比人们想象的现代化得多。

135
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,240
Where are you from?
你从哪里来？

136
00:05:04,240 --> 00:05:05,600
Well, let's see.
嗯，让我想想。

137
00:05:05,600 --> 00:05:09,760
I'm from Kansas originally, a much quieter and more peaceful place than here.
我原本来自堪萨斯州，那里比这里安静平和得多。

138
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:10,760
That's for sure.
确实如此。

139
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:11,760
Uh-huh.
嗯哼。

140
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:13,240
But I'm living in Paris right now.
但我现在住在巴黎。

141
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,240
Oh, Paris.
哦，巴黎。

142
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,240
That's wonderful.
那太棒了。

143
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:17,280
I'd love to visit sometime.
我希望能找个时间去参观。

144
00:05:17,280 --> 00:05:20,360
All right, we're back.
好了，我们回来了。

145
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:23,960
So now let's continue with some more phrases on Fluency Builder.
现在让我们继续学习流畅表达中的更多短语。

146
00:05:23,960 --> 00:05:26,720
Okay, this first phrase is one that I really like to use.
好的，第一个短语是我非常喜欢用的。

147
00:05:26,720 --> 00:05:29,120
The phrase is from Michelle.
这个短语来自米歇尔。

148
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:32,400
She says, you can say that again.
她说，你说得太对了。

149
00:05:32,400 --> 00:05:36,560
But she's talking about how Shanghai is so big and so exciting.
但她是在说上海有多大、多刺激。

150
00:05:36,560 --> 00:05:38,200
And Michelle says, you can say that again.
然后米歇尔说，你说得太对了。

151
00:05:38,200 --> 00:05:39,680
Now, what does this mean, Marco?
马可，这是什么意思？

152
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:40,680
That's right.
没错。

153
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:43,040
So she is basically agreeing with the person.
所以她基本上是在同意对方的话。

154
00:05:43,040 --> 00:05:45,040
The stranger says, Shanghai is amazing.
那个陌生人说，上海太棒了。

155
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,040
It's great.
它很棒。

156
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,200
There's so much to see.
有很多可看的东西。

157
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:49,240
Michelle says, you can say that again.
米歇尔说，你说得太对了。

158
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:51,080
It's saying, I agree with you.
这表示，我同意你。

159
00:05:51,080 --> 00:05:52,080
You are so right.
你说得太对了。

160
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,080
I really agree.
我真的很同意。

161
00:05:53,080 --> 00:05:55,920
All right, so this is very emphatic.
好的，所以这个表达非常强调。

162
00:05:55,920 --> 00:06:00,200
That means that it's really, it's more than just I agree.
这意味着它真的，不仅仅是“我同意”。

163
00:06:00,200 --> 00:06:01,520
I really, really agree.
我真的、真的同意。

164
00:06:01,520 --> 00:06:05,280
The person really feels something about this, feels passionately about it.
这个人对此事有强烈的感受，充满热情。

165
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:06,280
That's right.
没错。

166
00:06:06,280 --> 00:06:09,840
So if you go to the movies and you say, oh, that movie was terrible, you can say.
所以如果你去看电影，你说，哦，那部电影太糟糕了，你可以说。

167
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,200
You can say that again.
你说得对极了。

168
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,200
Exactly.
正是。

169
00:06:12,200 --> 00:06:13,200
It means, oh, I agree.
它的意思是，哦，我同意。

170
00:06:13,200 --> 00:06:15,000
It was really bad.
它真的很差。

171
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:16,000
That's right.
没错。

172
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:22,000
Now, when Michelle asked the stranger where he was from, he says, I'm from Kansas originally.
现在，当米歇尔问那个陌生人他是哪里人时，他说，我原本来自堪萨斯州。

173
00:06:22,000 --> 00:06:24,840
Okay, what's originally?
好的，“originally”是什么意思？

174
00:06:24,840 --> 00:06:25,840
I'm original?
我是原创的？

175
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:26,840
No.
不。

176
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:32,280
I'm from Kansas originally means maybe I don't live in Kansas now, but that's where I come
“我原本来自堪萨斯州”可能意味着我现在不住在堪萨斯州，但那是我来的地方。

177
00:06:32,280 --> 00:06:33,280
from.
来自。

178
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:35,560
Origin, originally.
起源，原本。

179
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:37,360
That means, you know, at the beginning.
这意味着，你知道，一开始。

180
00:06:37,360 --> 00:06:38,360
Right.
对。

181
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:43,720
And remember, Kansas, by the way, is one of the states in the United States.
记住，顺便说一下，堪萨斯州是美国的一个州。

182
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:47,760
And so he's saying he's from Kansas, but now he lives in Paris.
所以他说他来自堪萨斯州，但现在他住在巴黎。

183
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:53,200
So that's why you say, I'm originally from Kansas, but I live in Paris.
所以这就是为什么你说，我原本来自堪萨斯州，但我住在巴黎。

184
00:06:53,200 --> 00:06:57,800
All right, so Marco, you live here in Shanghai, but where do you come from originally?
好的，马可，你住在上海，但你原本来自哪里？

185
00:06:57,800 --> 00:06:59,760
Originally, I'm from Ecuador.
原本，我来自厄瓜多尔。

186
00:06:59,760 --> 00:07:00,880
All right.
好的。

187
00:07:00,880 --> 00:07:04,320
And I'm originally from Chicago, but I currently live in China.
我原本来自芝加哥，但我目前住在中国。

188
00:07:04,320 --> 00:07:05,320
That's right.
没错。

189
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,320
Okay.
好的。

190
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:13,280
And as he was talking about Kansas, he also said that, well, it's obviously a lot quieter
当他谈论堪萨斯州时，他还说，嗯，那里显然安静得多。

191
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,680
and more peaceful.
也更平和。

192
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:19,360
And then he ends his statement by saying, that's for sure.
然后他结束陈述时说，“那是肯定的”。

193
00:07:19,360 --> 00:07:20,360
That's for sure.
那是肯定的。

194
00:07:20,360 --> 00:07:24,540
And this is a phrase that we use to add emphasis on something.
这是一个我们用来强调某事的短语。

195
00:07:24,540 --> 00:07:30,240
It's almost like saying, this is a really quiet, much quieter and peaceful place.
这几乎就像在说，这真是一个安静得多、平和得多的地方。

196
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:31,240
That's for sure.
那是肯定的。

197
00:07:31,240 --> 00:07:32,960
It really is.
确实如此。

198
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:37,400
It's not like you're adding anything to the statement, like no meaning, but you're actually
并不是你在陈述中加了什么，比如没有新意思，但你实际上。

199
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,800
kind of making it more strong.
让它更有力了。

200
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:39,800
Right.
对。

201
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:40,880
You're saying it's a fact.
你在说这是一个事实。

202
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:41,880
It's a fact.
这是一个事实。

203
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:43,320
It's really this way.
它真的是这样。

204
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:47,560
So obviously, Kansas compared to Shanghai is a lot more quieter.
所以显然，堪萨斯州与上海相比安静得多。

205
00:07:47,560 --> 00:07:48,560
That's for sure.
那是肯定的。

206
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,560
Mm-hmm.
嗯哼。

207
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:54,760
Or I could say that in Chicago in the winter, it's a lot colder than Shanghai.
或者我可以说，在芝加哥的冬天，比上海冷得多。

208
00:07:54,760 --> 00:07:55,760
That's for sure.
那是肯定的。

209
00:07:55,760 --> 00:07:56,760
Right.
对。

210
00:07:56,760 --> 00:08:01,160
So again, you're emphasizing on your statement, telling everyone that it's very, very much
所以再次，你在强调你的陈述，告诉每个人它非常、非常。

211
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,160
like this.
像这样。

212
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:03,440
That's how it really is.
它真的是这样。

213
00:08:03,440 --> 00:08:04,440
Okay.
好的。

214
00:08:04,440 --> 00:08:06,680
So that's all the phrases we have for you.
所以这就是我们为你准备的所有短语。

215
00:08:06,680 --> 00:08:16,600
Why don't we listen to our dialogue one last time.
我们最后再听一遍对话吧。

216
00:08:16,600 --> 00:08:17,600
Excuse me.
打扰一下。

217
00:08:17,600 --> 00:08:18,600
Is this seat taken?
这个座位有人吗？

218
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,240
No, please feel free.
没有，请随意。

219
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,440
Thanks a lot.
非常感谢。

220
00:08:21,440 --> 00:08:23,040
Do you work in Shanghai?
你在上海工作吗？

221
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:24,040
Yes, I do.
是的，我工作。

222
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,040
How about you?
你呢？

223
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,920
No, I'm a tourist.
不，我是游客。

224
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:28,280
This place is amazing.
这个地方太棒了。

225
00:08:28,280 --> 00:08:31,120
It's much bigger than I imagined and much more exciting.
它比我想象的大得多，也刺激得多。

226
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:32,720
There's so much to see here.
这里有很多可看的东西。

227
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,520
You can say that again.
你说得对极了。

228
00:08:34,520 --> 00:08:37,480
It's much more modern than people imagine.
它比人们想象的现代得多。

229
00:08:37,480 --> 00:08:38,480
Where are you from?
你从哪里来？

230
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,840
Well, let's see.
嗯，让我想想。

231
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:44,040
I'm from Kansas originally, a much quieter and more peaceful place than here.
我原本来自堪萨斯州，一个比这里安静得多、平和得多的地方。

232
00:08:44,040 --> 00:08:45,040
That's for sure.
那是肯定的。

233
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:46,040
Uh-huh.
嗯哼。

234
00:08:46,040 --> 00:08:47,400
But I'm living in Paris right now.
但我现在住在巴黎。

235
00:08:47,400 --> 00:08:48,400
Oh, Paris.
哦，巴黎。

236
00:08:48,400 --> 00:08:49,400
Wonderful.
太棒了。

237
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:51,720
I'd love to visit sometime.
我希望有一天能去参观。

238
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:54,520
All right.
好的。

239
00:08:54,520 --> 00:08:56,080
So small talk with a stranger.
所以和陌生人闲聊。

240
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:59,160
This is actually a very common scenario.
这实际上是一个非常常见的场景。

241
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:03,240
If in a bus, in a train, you sit next to a stranger, this is more or less what you're
如果你在公交车或火车上坐在一个陌生人旁边，这差不多就是你们会聊的话题。

242
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,240
going to talk about.
要聊的内容。

243
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:05,240
Where are you from?
你从哪里来？

244
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,240
What do you do?
你是做什么的？

245
00:09:06,240 --> 00:09:07,240
Where do you live?
你住在哪里？

246
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,240
That's right.
没错。

247
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,000
And you don't even have to talk about this with a total stranger.
而且你甚至不需要和完全陌生的人聊这些。

248
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:14,960
You could actually use this with someone that you're working with or just an acquaintance.
你其实可以用这些话题和同事或熟人聊。

249
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:18,780
So basically, these are key questions that you would ask someone that you don't really
所以基本上，这些是你问不太熟悉的人时会问的关键问题。

250
00:09:18,780 --> 00:09:19,920
know very well.
不太了解的人。

251
00:09:19,920 --> 00:09:20,920
That's right.
没错。

252
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:24,840
And as you can see, you're not really going into any deep personal questions.
而且你看，你并没有深入问任何私人问题。

253
00:09:24,840 --> 00:09:30,400
It's very light conversation, very brief as well.
这是很轻松的对话，也很简短。

254
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,400
That's right.
没错。

255
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:35,260
And I would like to add that in American culture, people often think it's very rude to ask someone
我想补充一点，在美国文化中，人们通常认为问别人赚多少钱、公寓多少钱、车多少钱是非常粗鲁的。

256
00:09:35,260 --> 00:09:40,120
how much do you earn, how much is your apartment, how much is your car.
所以在美国文化中的闲聊里，我认为在很多西方文化中，我们不会谈论金钱或宗教。

257
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:45,480
So in small talk in American culture, and I think a lot of Western cultures, we don't
所以在美国文化中的闲聊里，我认为在很多西方文化中，我们不会谈论金钱或宗教。

258
00:09:45,480 --> 00:09:47,680
talk about money or religion.
所以在美国文化中的闲聊里，我认为在很多西方文化中，我们不会谈论金钱或宗教。

259
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:49,200
So what religion are you?
那你信什么教？

260
00:09:49,200 --> 00:09:55,280
So I think it's important to talk about things that are very simple.
所以我认为聊一些非常简单的事情很重要。

261
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,520
What do you do for a living?
你是做什么工作的？

262
00:09:56,520 --> 00:09:58,080
Where do you live?
你住在哪里？

263
00:09:58,080 --> 00:09:59,080
How's the weather?
天气怎么样？

264
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,080
These things.
这些话题。

265
00:10:00,080 --> 00:10:01,080
Yes.
是的。

266
00:10:01,080 --> 00:10:03,400
This is exactly, I think, one of the main points that when you're learning a language
我认为这恰恰是学习英语这类语言时的一个重点，不仅要理解语言，还要理解文化。

267
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:07,580
such as English, not only to understand the language, but also the culture.
这非常非常不同，尤其是在亚洲文化中，比如你去理发店，理发师问你赚多少钱，这没什么大不了的。

268
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:11,680
It's very, very different, especially, for example, in Asian cultures where it's no big
这非常非常不同，尤其是在亚洲文化中，比如你去理发店，理发师问你赚多少钱，这没什么大不了的。

269
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:17,220
deal if you go to the hairdresser and the hairdresser asks you how much you earn.
这非常非常不同，尤其是在亚洲文化中，比如你去理发店，理发师问你赚多少钱，这没什么大不了的。

270
00:10:17,220 --> 00:10:21,520
But in the United States or many Western countries, it's not something that you talk about your
但在美国或许多西方国家，谈论薪水或直接问这种事是不合适的。

271
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:23,280
salary or that you really ask.
但在美国或许多西方国家，谈论薪水或直接问这种事是不合适的。

272
00:10:23,280 --> 00:10:25,640
It's kind of personal information.
这算是私人信息。

273
00:10:25,640 --> 00:10:26,640
It is.
是的。

274
00:10:26,640 --> 00:10:29,920
And if you talk about it, you might make people very uncomfortable.
如果你聊这些，可能会让人很不舒服。

275
